		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2018 SI"></a><br><code>sle2018s/paper01</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2018 SI</a> paper:</span><br><i>Relational Reference Attribute Grammars: Improving continuous model validation</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/JohannesMey.html">Johannes Mey</a>, <a href="../profile/RenéSchöne.html">René Schöne</a>, <a href="../profile/GörelHedin.html">Görel Hedin</a>, <a href="../profile/EmmaSöderberg.html">Emma Söderberg</a>, <a href="../profile/ThomasKühn.html">Thomas Kühn</a>, <a href="../profile/NiklasFors.html">Niklas Fors</a>, <a href="../profile/JesperÖqvist.html">Jesper Öqvist</a>, <a href="../profile/UweAßmann.html">Uwe Aßmann</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cola.2019.100940">10.1016/j.cola.2019.100940</a></li>
<li>Extended version of <a href="../sle2018/paper12.html"><em>Continuous model validation using reference attribute grammars</em></a> (SLE 2018)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagM">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> The paper extends Reference Attribute Grammars with first-class relations (“Relational RAGs”), advancing a meta-language framework for defining incremental analyses over models/ASTs.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It is realised in a RAG toolchain (JastAdd) with engineering for demand-driven, incremental evaluation plus persistence/serialization support.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagL">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> Its central scenario is continuous validation under ongoing model edits, addressing maintenance-like concerns through incremental recomputation strategies.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> It reports empirical results (e.g., on benchmarked models/strategies) to quantify performance and responsiveness trade-offs for incremental validation.
</li></ul></li></ul>
		<clear/>
		<footer/>
	</body>
